This paper deals with the creation and evaluation of language models, specifically word embedding models, for relation extraction tasks in the digital humanities domain. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models for training and evaluation, which could fall under cs.DL (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evaluation of the models involves analyzing the impact of corpus term frequencies and task difficulty on accuracy, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Learning).
